%U A395994 6,10,6,10,10,13,3,6,2,18,2,16,8,8,8,18,2
%N A395994 Number of fractions k/n, with 1 <= k <= n and GCD(n,k) = 1, whose greedy Egyptian fraction representation has more terms than the shortest representation of k/n as a sum of unit fractions.
%C A395994 Number of integers k in 1..n such that GCD(n,k) = 1 and A097847(n,k) < A050205(n,k).
%H A395994 Pontus von Brömssen, <a href="/A395994/b395994.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..2500</a>
%H A395994 <a href="/index/Ed#Egypt">Index entries for sequences related to Egyptian fractions</a>.
%F A395994 a(n) = 0 if and only if n is in A396000.
%e A395994 For n = 34, 25/34 is the only fraction (in lowest terms) with denominator 34 for which the greedy Egyptian fraction representation has more terms than the shortest representation, so a(34) = 1. This is true also for 8/34 = 4/17 but since 8 and 34 have a common factor, 8/34 is not counted by a(34).
%e A395994 For n = 35, the a(35) = 6 fractions are 16/35, 26/35, 27/35, 29/35, 32/35, and 34/35.
%Y A395994 Cf. A050205, A097847, A395995, A395996, A395997, A395998, A395999, A396000, A396001.
%K A395994 nonn,new
%O A395994 1,19
%A A395994 _Pontus von Brömssen_, May 14 2026
